ThinkPart(
    type='think',
    think="Now I have a complete picture. Let me identify the issues:\n\n1. **To
pInfoBar.ts - UIIcon missing texture**: The `UIIcon` components in `TopInfoBar` 
don't pass a `texture` parameter, so they'll render as fallback rectangles inste
ad of the intended emojis/icons. This is a functional regression from the old co
de which displayed emoji icons (`💰`, `🪵`, `⛏️`, `👷`). Since `UIIcon` supports 
`texture` but no text/emoji fallback, the emojis are lost.\n\n2. **BuildingSelec
tor.ts - lost icons**: Similarly, the old `BuildingSelector` had emoji icons for
each building type (⚡, 🌲, ⛏️, etc.). The new `UIList`-based implementation only
shows text labels without icons. This is a UI regression.\n\n3. **ConfirmationDi
alog.ts - confirmColor ignored**: The `confirmColor` config property is accepted
in `ConfirmationDialogConfig` but is never passed to `UIDialog`. Since `UIDialog
` hardcodes `UITheme.cinnabarRed` for confirm button, the custom color is lost. 
Minor API regression.\n\n4. **RemoveConfirmDialog.ts / UpgradeConfirmDialog.ts -
double destroy risk**: In `destroy()`, they call `this.panel?.destroy()` before 
`super.destroy()`. Since `UIPanel` is a child of the container, `super.destroy()
` will also destroy children. This could cause double-destroy issues or null ref
erence errors in Phaser. This is a potential bug.\n\n5. **TopInfoBar.ts - setAva
tar texture orphaning**: When `setAvatar` is called, it does `this.avatarContain
er.removeAll(true)` which destroys previous children, then adds a new image. But
the initial `avatarBg` and `avatarIcon` are destroyed. This means subsequent cal
ls to `setAvatar` work, but if called with a non-existent texture, nothing happe
ns. The original code likely had the same behavior though, so not a new issue.\n
\n6. **BuildingSelector.ts - clearSelection doesn't clear UIList highlight**: `c
learSelection()` only sets `selectedBuildingId = null` but doesn't tell `buildin
gList` to clear its selection highlight. The old code cleared `selectedMark` on 
all items. This is a functional bug - the UI will still show an item as selected
after `clearSelection()` is called.\n\n7. **ConfirmationDialog.ts - show() doesn
't update title/message**: The `show(config)` method accepts partial config but 
notes that title/message can't be updated. If a caller passes new title/message,
they'll be silently ignored while callbacks are updated. This inconsistency coul
d confuse consumers.\n\n8. **UpgradeConfirmDialog.ts - `showInsufficientResource
s` position calculation**: The warning text y-position is calculated as `this.pa
nel.getContentBounds().y + this.panel.getContentBounds().height - 10`. Since `ge
tContentBounds()` returns a rectangle relative to the panel's local coordinates,
and the warning text is added to `this.panel` via `addContent`, the positioning 
should work, but calling `getContentBounds()` twice is slightly inefficient. Not
a major issue.\n\nLet me also check if there's test coverage for these changed f
iles.",
    encrypted=None
)
